com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Session, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Field, ValueNode

    public abstract class Node
extends Object
implements Session, Serializable
    Node is the base class for all persistent data in Data Pipeline. It is the superclass for records, fields, arrays, and values.
    See Also:
    Record, Field, ArrayValue, SingleValue, ValueNode, Serialized Form

      • isChildNode

        public boolean isChildNode()
        Indicates if this record has a parent record (i.e. this record is part of a hierarchical structure). If this method returns true, getParentField() can be used to retrieve the parent record's field that this record is attached to.
        See Also:
        getParentField(), getParentRecord(), hasChildRecords(), #getRecordDepth(), Field.getValueAsRecord(), Field#getValueAsRecords()

      • getNodeDepth

        public int getNodeDepth()
        Returns this node's distance from its root node. It returns 0 if it is the root node (i.e. it has no parents), 1 if it is the direct child of the root node, 2 if it is the grandchild of the root, and so on.
